#: ../../website/optimize/seo.rst:94
msgid ""
"To address this issue, all CSS / Less / Sass files are concatenated into "
"a single .CSS file to send to the browser. So a visitor has **only one "
".CSS file to load** per page, which is particularly efficient. As the CSS"
" is shared amongst all pages, when the visitor clicks on another page, "
"the browser does not even have to load a new CSS file!"
